sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Original chiA sequence originates from GQ855217.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part uses a pBAD promoter (BBa_I0500), weak RBS (BBa_B0032) and a double terminator (BBa_B0015). When induced with arabinose, it will produce chiA. A weak promoter was chosen to prevent formation of inclusion bodies during expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a composite part for expression of the chiA protein coding region from BBa_K1913000.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lisa R??ttjers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of this part is chiA from Serratia marcescens GEI; accession GQ855217.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Serratia marcescens GEI chiA protein coding region optimized for BioBrick use. This part is useful for breaking down chitin polymers. The strain of origin has been isolated from the Chinese honey bee and showed virulence towards Varroa destructor. Chitinases A and B from the strain were found to have miticidal activity. ChiA has both exochitinase and endochitinase activity. This protein is known to show synergistic activity with ChiB. ChiA can potentially be used to control Varroa destructor mite populations, as mite mortality increases when the mites are subjected to filter paper incubated with purified chiA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence was optimized using the IDT codon optimization tool. Multiple restriction sites were removed; BsaI at position 195, PstI at position 644, PstI at position 905 and EcoRI at position 943. Additionally, several antisense stop codons were introduced to prevent antisense transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lisa R??ttjers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
